title: Starfish Space raises $14 million for in-orbit servicers
summary: Starfish Space has raised $14 million for its planned satellite life extension and debris removal service in a funding round led by insurance giant Munich Re, the startup announced March 8.

title: Watch live: Relativity Space to launch first 3D-printed, methane-fueled orbital rocket
summary: Relativity Space, a California-based startup that counts billionaire Mark Cuban as one of its early investors, will try to launch the first 3D-printed, methane-fueled rocket into orbit from Cape Canaveral Wednesday. The Terran 1 rocket’s first test flight has a three-hour launch window opening at 1 p.m. EST (1800 GMT).

title: Relativity Space will attempt to become a real rocket company today
summary: Relativity Space is one of the more intriguing new space launch companies.

title: Relativity Space set for maiden launch of Terran 1 rocket
summary: Relativity Space is preparing to conduct the first launch of its Terran 1 rocket Wednesday, in an attempt to become the first 3D-printed and methane-fueled rocket to reach orbit. The Good Luck, Have Fun (GLHF) mission is scheduled for liftoff from Launch Complex 16 (LC-16) at the Cape Canaveral Space Force Station during a three-hour launch window opening at 1 PM EST (18:00 UTC).

title: Shield Capital adds retired general Goldfein to national security advisory board
summary: Shield Capital, a venture firm that invests in defense and space startups, announced that retired U.S. Air Force general David Goldfein has joined its national security advisory board.

title: NASA studying unexpected performance of Orion’s heat shield ahead of crew mission
summary: "Vigilance is very important for us as we fly crew going forward."

title: ISS dodges commercial imaging satellite
summary: The International Space Station adjusted its orbit March 6 to avoid a close approach by an imaging satellite operated by Satellogic, the latest evidence of growing congestion in low Earth orbit.

title: Launch day timeline for Relativity Space’s Terran 1 rocket
summary: Relativity Space’s 10-story-tall Terran 1 rocket will encounter the most extreme aerodynamic forces of its eight-minute test flight around 80 seconds after liftoff from Cape Canaveral. That’s a key moment when the company’s engineers hope to confirm the 3D-printed rocket can withstand the rigors of launch.

title: NASA Preparing Final ISS Commercial Cargo Delivery Contracts
summary: NASA is proposing to extend three existing contracts for the transportation of cargo to and from the International Space Station (ISS) through its anticipated end in 2030. The contracts, which were originally awarded in 2015, are currently set to expire in 2024.

title: SpaceX Introduces £15 Per Month Starlink Rental Offer in UK
summary: SpaceX has announced a new initiative to make its Starlink internet service more accessible to potential customers in the United Kingdom (UK).
